Cape Town - Located in the centre of the city, the Taj Hotel boasts a strong sense of place and is within walking distance to some of South Africa’s foremost landmarks and attractions. Surrounded by an eclectic array of shops, galleries and restaurants, and spread across two heritage buildings, all 176 rooms of the 5-star hotel feature breathtaking views of the city and the iconic Table Mountain. The hotel’s one-and two-bedroom suites are perfect for the discerning traveller or for families. “We offer an array of dining experiences. Bombay Brasserie offers sit-down à la carte dining where patrons can enjoy pre-dinner drinks from the huge range of cocktails, beers, wines and a collection of the finest whiskies and brandies.  “Taj Cape Town will serve you everything of the best,” says marketing officer Liza Nieuwoudt. This Valentine’s Day, charm your special someone with a romantic dinner at one of your favourite Taj restaurants. Taj Cape Town is giving away two romantic dinners; one for a couple at The Mint Restaurant & Lobby during an evening valued at R990.00 and another dinner experience for a couple at Bombay Brasserie valued at R1 290.00. To enter, tell us in 100 words how you’ll spoil the love of your life this Valentine’s Day. Email your entries to arglet@inl.co.za with your name, address and cellphone number. The competition closed at 3pm today. Winners will be notified shortly after that. Ts & Cs apply. Winners’ names will also be published on Monday. Cape Argus